> alt just delegate to `scroll_up_by(1)`.

This would be cleaner code, but these functions have different behaviors when `selected` is `None`.

Here's a quick test I wrote to demonstrate.
```rs
#[test]
fn state_naviagtion_when_select_is_none() {
    let mut state = ListState::default();
    state.select_previous();
    assert_eq!(state.selected, Some(usize::MAX));
                                                  
    let mut state = ListState::default();
    state.scroll_up_by(1);
    assert_eq!(state.selected, Some(0));
}
```

I don't know this project well enough to know if this change would be desirable or not.

